 a\nfactor 2-3. This points towards both a similar chemical composition and\nexcitation of most of the COMs over these massive cores, which span about an\norder of magnitude in core mass. In contrast, CH3CCH emission is found to\npreferentially trace more the envelope, with a temperature ranging from 50 K to\n90 K. Core 1, the most massive hot core of W43-MM1, shows a richer line\nspectrum than the other cores. In core 2, the emission of O-bearing molecules\ndoes not peak at the dust continuum core center; the blue and red shifted\nemission correspond to the outflow lobes, suggesting a formation via the\nsublimation of the ice mantles through shocks or UV irradiation on the walls of\nthe cavity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Jul 2022 19:04:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-21"}
